"China&rsquo;s coal-fired power plants generated 59.6 percent of the country&rsquo;s electricity in the first half of 2024. China&rsquo;s coal-fired generation from January to June was 2,793.5 terawatt hours, which was 2.4 percent higher than the same months in 2023 and the highest amount for the first half of the year since at least 2015."<br> <br>

"Power sector carbon dioxide emissions from the use of fossil fuels was 2.826 billion metric tons during the first half of 2024&ndash;2.4 percent higher than the same months in 2023."<br> <br>

"China&rsquo;s imports of thermal coal from the seaborne market, used mainly to generate electricity, were 168.73 million metric tons in the first six months of the year, up 8.5 percent from 155.51 million in the same period in 2023. This was the strongest first half in China&rsquo;s history."<br> <br>

"China&rsquo;s coal production rebounded in June, with output of all grades of coal rising to a six-month high of 405.38 million tons, which was 3.6 percent above the same month in 2023."</p></div></div>
